(1) A person shall not be qualified for election as a councillor if he— (a) is, under any law in force in Zambia, adjudged or declared to be of unsound mind; (b) is under sentence of death imposed on him by any court in Zambia or a sentence of imprisonment has been imposed on him by that court or is substituted by a competent authority for some other sentence imposed on him by that court; (c) is an undischarged bankrupt, adjudged or declared bankrupt under any law in force in Zambia, or has made a composition or arrangement with his creditors and has not paid his debts in full; (d) is an officer or an employee of a council ; (e) has on the day, for nomination or of election to the council , not paid the rate, charge or tax due to the council or to any other Local Authority and has been notified; or (f) is an election officer .
